  help  Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
      --database-url <DATABASE_URL>
          Database URL (`SQLite` or Postgres)
          
          [default: sqlite:tanren.db]

      --phase <PHASE>
          Phase name used for capability enforcement and audit trail.
          
          Defaults to `cli-admin`, which is not a registered phase and so resolves to default-deny unless `TANREN_PHASE_CAPABILITIES` is explicitly provided.
          
          [default: cli-admin]

      --log-level <LOG_LEVEL>
          Log level filter (e.g. "info", "debug")
          
          [default: warn]

      --spec-folder <SPEC_FOLDER>
          Spec folder root used for runtime `phase-events.jsonl` appends. Required for mutating commands

      --actor-token-stdin
          Read actor JWT from stdin (preferred for secret-safe invocation)

      --spec-id <SPEC_ID>
          Canonical spec identity bound to this mutation session. Required for mutating commands

      --actor-token-file <ACTOR_TOKEN_FILE>
          Read actor JWT from this file path

      --agent-session-id <AGENT_SESSION_ID>
          Agent session id to stamp in `phase-events.jsonl` lines when `--spec-folder` is provided
          
          [default: cli-session]

      --actor-public-key-file <ACTOR_PUBLIC_KEY_FILE>
          Path to Ed25519 public key PEM for actor token verification

      --methodology-config <METHODOLOGY_CONFIG>
          Path to `tanren.yml` used to load `methodology.task_complete_requires`
          
          [default: tanren.yml]

      --token-issuer <TOKEN_ISSUER>
          Required JWT issuer claim

      --token-audience <TOKEN_AUDIENCE>
          Required JWT audience claim

      --actor-token-max-ttl-secs <ACTOR_TOKEN_MAX_TTL_SECS>
          Maximum allowed actor token lifetime (`exp - iat`) in seconds
          
          [default: 900]

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')

